real quark matter there\nexists the (approximate) duality between CSB and charged PC. Moreover, we can\nreverse the logic and we can predict the increase of pseudo-critical\ntemperature with chiral chemical potential, the much debated effect recently,\njust by the duality notion, hence bolster confidence in this result (lattice\nQCD showed this feature for unphysically large pion mass) and put it on the\nconsiderably more solid ground.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Dec 2018 14:37:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Feb 2019 10:13:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-27"}
